OFDR_PINN_Demodulation Technical Status Summary (ASCII)
Date: 2026-03-12

1) Project objective
- Task: regress target grating center wavelength shift (delta lambda) from 1D overlapped OFDR/UWFBG spectra.
- Focus: all-identical UWFBG overlap distortion, including neighbor relative shift, linewidth change, and local artifacts.
- Primary difficult benchmark currently used in method enhancement: phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3.

2) Benchmark and evaluation protocol currently in use
- Dataset path (hardest main case): data/processed/dataset_c_phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3.npz
- Main compare output root: results/phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3/
- Reported metrics: RMSE, MAE, P95, P99, R2.
- Fair compare rule (kept in recent runs): same dataset, same epochs/patience, same batch size, same optimizer/scheduler behavior, same CNN backbone unless explicitly testing a new model class.

3) New technical additions completed on 2026-03-12

3.1) New model: minimal CNN + BiLSTM regressor
- File: src/ofdr/models/phase3_cnn.py
- New class: CNNBiLSTMRegressor
- New model key: cnn_bilstm
- Integration path:
  - src/ofdr/models/phase3_cnn.py (build_model supports cnn_bilstm)
  - src/phase3/runner.py (reads model params when method_key == cnn_bilstm)
  - src/phase3/run_cnn_bilstm.py (entry script)
  - config/phase3_cnn_bilstm.yaml (minimal config)
  - config/phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3_method_bilstm.yaml
  - src/phase4a/run_method_enhance_cnn_vs_bilstm.py
- Shape flow in forward:
  - input: [B, N]
  - CNN features: [B, C, L]
  - transpose for LSTM: [B, L, C]
  - 1-layer bidirectional LSTM output: [B, L, 2H]
  - mean pool over sequence length: [B, 2H]
  - linear head: [B]
- Implementation constraints respected: reuse baseline CNN feature blocks; exactly 1 BiLSTM layer; no attention/transformer.

3.2) New training strategy (no backbone change): tail optimization
- Core file: src/ofdr/training/phase3_train_utils.py
- New loss option:
  - name: tail_aware_l1
  - formula: L_i = |e_i| + lambda_tail * max(0, |e_i| - tau)^2
  - defaults used: tau=0.01, lambda_tail=3.0
- New hard sample weighting option (training only):
  - formula: w_i = 1 + alpha * I(|e_i| > tau_hard)
  - weighted per-sample loss: w_i * L_i
  - defaults used: tau_hard=0.01, alpha=1.5
- New hardest-case runner:
  - src/phase4a/run_method_enhance_cnn_tailaware.py
- New configs:
  - config/phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3_method_tailaware_baseline.yaml
  - config/phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3_method_tailaware.yaml
  - config/phase4a_shift004_linewidth_l3_method_tailaware_hard.yaml

